  "instruction": "Build a Generative UI mini-site in VS Code. Create the folder /home/user/Desktop/generative_ui_scene with files index.html, styles.css, app.js, manifest.json, and assets/hero.jpg + assets/logo.svg. First download two images from these websites into assets/: (1) https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/08/HERO.png -> hero.jpg, (2) https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/a7/React-icon.svg -> logo.svg. Then implement a single-page dashboard with: a hero section (id=\"hero\") that displays assets/hero.jpg, a timeline section (id=\"timeline\"), and a canvas chart (id=\"chartCanvas\") rendered by app.js using monthlyRevenue = [120, 180, 150, 210, 260]. In app.js, render bars on canvas and also draw logo.svg onto the chart as a watermark (drawImage). Use local image paths only (no remote image URLs inside final html/css/js). In manifest.json, include project=\"generative-ui\", theme=\"aurora\", chartType=\"bar\", and required_images containing both asset paths.",
  "source": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial | authors",
